<br>
<br>
Because they still may be the best belt for a druid.  Moreover, some guilds do have point systems where a druid that builds up enough points could potentially be awarded a haste belt.  I have a lower level haste belt myself.<br>
<br>
Moreover, the argument about some items not being attainable could apply to many of the top items, which 95% of the druids in the game probably never have a chance of seeing.  That's really beyond the scope of what I am doing.  I just put them out there, and pretty much leave considerations of attainability up to each individual to assess.<br>
